PATCH: Remove custom mobile style and adjust metrics and email sending
This commit removes the custom style block for mobile devices from app.blade.php. It also updates the condition for displaying metric values in metric.blade.php and augments the sendEmail function in SendEmail.php to fill email data from the request.

PATCH: Enhanced exception handling and email sending features
The changes involve adding more exceptions to the list of unreported exceptions in the Handler.php. Also, the code in SendEmail.php has been adjusted, including adding fields for query and subject in the email form. A new TempMail model also has been created to better organize and handle temporary emails.

PATCH: Update SendEmail layout format
Refactored the layout construction of the SendEmail page in Orchid. Replaced the old structure of the form with the Layout::rows() method, which groups the entire form into a single row, improving visibility and making it easier to add or remove fields. The overall code readability is improved and layout now allows for a more flexible design.

PATCH: Add customizable email creation functionality and views
Implemented functionality allowing for the creation and customization of emails using the DefaultEmail class. A 'Send Email' page was also integrated into the admin section. All content and layout templates for support messages and order shipping notifications were updated for enhanced user experience.

PATCH: Change visibility conditions for event action buttons
Visibility conditions for 'update', 'cancel', 'undo' and 'finish' buttons in EventsEditScreen.php have been updated. This ensures that the buttons are only shown when the event status is either 'INCOMING' or 'STARTED', providing a more intuitive user interface.
